c/p\u003e\n              \n\n\n  \n\n              \u003cp\u003eAnyone who has lived anywhere else will tell you that this is not typical. The folk knowledge used to explain the concentration of high quality bagels has become gospel: \u003ca href=\"https://qz.com/263351/the-secret-of-new-york-citys-mythic-bagel-baking-water\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eit’s all about the water\u003c/a\u003e, that there’s something about the pH or the mineral content in NYC tap water that causes the city’s dough to be intangibly superior.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eI’ve always been skeptical of this notion, but a little research shows it’s simply not true. \u003ca href=\"https://www.americastestkitchen.com/access/welcome5?extcode=KGBAM0020\u0026amp;utm_medium=cpc\u0026amp;utm_source=google\u0026amp;utm_campaign=Brand%7CAmerica%27s_Test_Kitchen%7CPhr-Ext\u0026amp;utm_term=america%27s%20test%20kitchen\u0026amp;utm_content=sTAYVTOjt%7Cpcrid%7C700507733926%7Cpkw%7Camerica%27s%20test%20kitchen%7Cpdv%7Cc%7Cpmt%7Ce%7Cproductid%7C%7Cpgrid%7C165692544871%7Ccpgnid%7C21322604783%7Cptaid%7Ckwd-103943123%7Cadext%7C%7C\u0026amp;mt_dimension_1=Search-B\u0026amp;mt_dimension_2=Google\u0026amp;mt_dimension_3=Digital-Sub\u0026amp;gad_source=1\u0026amp;gclid=CjwKCAiA-ty8BhA_EiwAkyoa35yIcRmmDuhxG26moEayxp0UrzDy5lX0iwI7K0LTZmxDRzVwb4PvehoCBGMQAvD_BwE\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAmerica’s Test Kitchen\u003c/a\u003e conducted a \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XjAy0rAOCE0\" target=\"_blank\"\u003etaste test\u003c/a\u003e, pitting bagels made with both Boston and New York City municipal water against each other. The results amongst tasters showed the two batches to be virtually indistinguishable.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button\" data-pin-do=\"buttonPin\" data-pin-media=\"\" data-pin-custom=\"true\" data-ga-event=\"inPageInteraction\" data-ga-event-action=\"Pinterest Share\" dat